  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bursa Hospital PPP</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The EBRD is financing a hospital infrastructure PPP project involving the  design, construction, equipping, financing, and maintenance of an integrated  health campus in Bursa, Turkey, pursuant to a 28-year concession awarded by  Turkey&apos;s Ministry of Health (&quot;MoH&quot;). Under this PPP structure, the  concessionaire will supply and maintain the hospital facilities, while the  provision of medical care and services will remain the responsibility of the  MoH. Total project costs are estimated at around EUR 513 million.  Bursa Hospital PPP campus will comprise three buildings with a total bed  capacity of 1,355: a general hospital (275 beds), cardiology (275 beds),  oncology (252 beds), maternity/paediatric (253 beds), physical therapy and  rehabilitation (200 beds), and high security forensic psychiatric (100 beds).</narrative>
  </description>
